description:
TPO/2019/1009 work to trees

T306 cherry. Remove fractured branch.  Reduce crown by 1-2 metres.  Reason - risk management.

310 horse chestnut.  Reduce crown by 1-2 metres all over.  Reason - risk management.

331 hornbeam.  Reduce spread on building side to achieve clearance of 1.5m from building.  Reason - improve relationship between tree and building

332 cherry.  Remove fractured branch.  Reason - risk management

831A.  Plum.  Remove near-dead tree.  Reason - risk management

392 Blue Atlas cedar.  Reduce height by 1-2 metres and reduce spread of lateral branches by 2-3 metres.  Crown thin by 20%.  Reason - improve relationship between tree and building

393 Blue Atlas cedar.  Reduce height by 1-2 metres and reduce spread of lateral branches by 2 metres.  Crown thin by 20%.  Reason - improve relationship between tree and building

Note - other work is proposed which is exempt from statutory control, including removal of dead trees, and removal of dead branches from living trees.  Refer to report.
application_type_full: Tree works: Trees in conservation areas/subject to TPOs
